<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,509,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Ecology and Phenology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi" authorityYear="2012" box="[538,851,306,331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligusticum">
<emphasis box="[538,851,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Leucanthemum ligusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in open rocky places (
<quantity box="[1223,1380,306,332]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="10.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="630.0" valueMax="1060.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1060 m</quantity>
), on siliceous substrates and deep-oceanic siliceous sedimentary rocks (&quot;diaspri&quot;). It is a hemicryptophyte, flowering from the beginning of May until the first half of July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,422,448]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi" authorityYear="2012" box="[390,706,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligusticum">
<emphasis box="[390,706,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Leucanthemum ligusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known from few localities in eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[1349,1435,422,448]" country="Italy" name="Liguria" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Liguria</collectingRegion>
(provinces of Genova and La Spezia; 
<figureCitation box="[616,690,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,244,1242,1263]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,609,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-467@4.[151,1436,609,1252]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leucanthemum ligusticum sp. nov. Known geographical distribution in eastern Liguria (northwestern Italy Italy)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065882/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Besides the three studied populations, the new species was observed near Bargone (Genova province), Mounts Roccagrande-Tregìn, 
<quantity box="[1056,1194,500,526]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="625.0" valueMax="850.0" valueMin="400.0">400–850 m</quantity>
and near the top of Mount Verruga, at 
<quantity box="[372,464,538,564]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="1060.0">1060 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065882" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5065882" box="[151,1357,1242,1264]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065882/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" startId="4.[151,244,1242,1263]" targetBox="[166,1423,609,1225]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1357,1242,1264]" box="[151,1357,1242,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1242,1263]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi, 2012" authorityName="Melai &amp; Marchetti &amp; Bernardello &amp; Peruzzi" authorityYear="2012" box="[274,526,1243,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligusticum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[274,526,1243,1264]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Leucanthemum ligusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[532,607,1243,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Known geographical distribution in eastern Liguria (northwestern Italy Italy).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1311,1503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,1311,1337]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Karyology:</emphasis>
—The new species is diploid, with 2n = 18 chromosomes, at all three localities studied (
<collectingRegion box="[159,252,1353,1379]" country="Italy" name="Liguria" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Liguria</collectingRegion>
; 
<figureCitation box="[265,397,1353,1379]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,248,1852,1873]" captionTargetBox="[151,1387,191,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-64@5.[151,1436,191,1831]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leucanthemum ligusticum sp. nov. Examples of metaphasic plates and relative haploid idiograms, from Ponte di Lagoscuro (A, D), Rocche di Valletti (B, E) and Rocchetta di Vara (C, F). Scale bars of metaphasic plates = 10 µm; scale bars of haploid idiograms = 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065886/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). The karyotype formula is 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[922,960,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[960,979,1349,1363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[1009,1046,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="4.0">4m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[1080,1118,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1118,1137,1349,1363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[1170,1208,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="8.0">8m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[1241,1279,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1279,1298,1349,1363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
at Ponte di Lagoscuro, 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[469,506,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[506,524,1391,1405]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[555,591,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[622,660,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="4.0">4m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[660,678,1391,1405]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[708,746,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="4.0">4m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[776,814,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[814,832,1391,1405]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[862,899,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="4.0">4m</quantity>
at Rocche di Valletti and 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[1381,1418,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1418,1436,1410,1424]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</subScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[175,213,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[212,230,1435,1449]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[258,296,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[328,366,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[365,383,1435,1449]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[415,453,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="6.0">6m</quantity>
+ 
<quantity box="[484,522,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[522,540,1435,1449]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[571,609,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="2.0">2m</quantity>
at Rocchetta di Vara (
<figureCitation box="[870,998,1439,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,248,1852,1873]" captionTargetBox="[151,1387,191,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-64@5.[151,1436,191,1831]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leucanthemum ligusticum sp. nov. Examples of metaphasic plates and relative haploid idiograms, from Ponte di Lagoscuro (A, D), Rocche di Valletti (B, E) and Rocchetta di Vara (C, F). Scale bars of metaphasic plates = 10 µm; scale bars of haploid idiograms = 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5065886/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
). Chromosome size ranges from 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="3.6">3.60 to 6.5 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
